{"id":28039,"title":"Serotonin syndrome.","abstract":"Serotonin syndrome is a potentially serious clinical condition. In this article, the authors put serotonin syndrome into historical context, discuss its pathophysiology, review in detail its clinical presentations, diagnostic criteria, differential diagnosis and treatment. Special attention is given to drugs that most often cause serotonin syndrome, and the gene polymorphisms involved in the metabolism of these drugs. ","date":"2014-08-07","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25038602","annotations":[{"name":"Serotonin","weight":0.852356,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serotonin"},{"name":"Gene","weight":0.847996,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene"},{"name":"Differential diagnosis","weight":0.812569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_diagnosis"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.748309,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Serotonin syndrome","weight":0.7371,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serotonin_syndrome"},{"name":"Pathophysiology","weight":0.734035,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathophysiology"},{"name":"Metabolism","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolism"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.688235,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.683726,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Polymorphism (biology)","weight":0.682468,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polymorphism_(biology)"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.542761,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"History","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.0136738,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"}]}
